{"lemma":"عَتِيقٌ","slug":"عَتِيقٌ","root":"ع.ت.ق","root_slug":"ع-ت-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ت-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَتِيق","root":"عتق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27964"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"antique, ancient, archaic, old","examples":[{"text":"ثُمَّ لْيَقْضُوا تَفَثَهُمْ وَلْيُوفُوا نُذُورَهُمْ وَلْيَطَّوَّفُوا بِالْبَيْتِ الْعَتِيقِ","english":"Then let them end their untidiness and fulfill their vows and perform tawaf around the ancient House."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"emancipated, free"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Belongs to the root ع ت ق (ʕ t q). Cognates with Aramaic עַתִּיק (ʿattīq), Hebrew עַתִּיק (ʿattīq) and Phoenician 𐤏𐤕𐤒 (ʿtq)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.tiːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27964","headword_ar":"عَتِيقٌ","root":"Etq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that precedes, outstrips,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outgoes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAtiqN","text_ar":"عَاتِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or this signifies a horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that precedes, and becomes safe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"secure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA; [see 1, first and second sentences;]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that precedes, outstrips,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outgoes, the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horses:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and the former, a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or an"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"horse: (Msb, TA:) or a horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift and excellent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that excites admiration by his generousness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAy^iEN","text_ar":"رَايِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, O, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EitaAqN","text_ar":"عِتَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqapN","text_ar":"عَتِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a young she-camel means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous, excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EitaAqN","text_ar":"عِتَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has this meaning applied to camels, (TA,) or to such as are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroHabiy~aAt","text_ar":"اَرْحَبِيَّات"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) and to horses; (K, TA;) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EitaAq","text_ar":"عِتَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"of horses are the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; and so of birds; (Mgh;) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof, in a sense wider that that in which this epithet is applied in English falconry;] or of birds,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as prey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqN","text_ar":"عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being applied to one of them: (TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EitaAqu AlT~ayori","text_ar":"عِتَاقُ الطَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied [particularly] to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eagles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqaAbN","text_ar":"عُقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatiyqu AlT~ayori","text_ar":"عَتِيقُ الطَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hawk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falcon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqN","text_ar":"عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) and anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) thus applied to a hawk, and dates, and water, and fat: (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEatiyqu","text_ar":"العَتِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dates"},{"kind":"text","text":"[themselves], (AHn, O, K,) as in a verse of 'Antarah (or of Khuzaz-Ibn-Lowdhán, S, TA) cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aba","text_ar":"كَذَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) as a proper name thereof; (K;) or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dates termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ihoriyz","text_ar":"شِهْرِيز"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EutuqN","text_ar":"عُتُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water"},{"kind":"text","text":"[itself]: (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat"},{"kind":"text","text":"[itself]: and accord. to IAar, anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has attained the utmost degree in goodness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"badness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beauty"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ugliness"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqN","text_ar":"عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EutuqN","text_ar":"عُتُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beautiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comely:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Eatiyqu Alwajohi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ عَتِيقُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is beautiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comely, in respect of the face"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN EatiyqapN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ عَتِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman beautiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comely; generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And (applied to a man, S, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delicate, in his external skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"after having been coarse and rough. (S, O, K.) ―         -b4-  And, applied to a slave, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Freed from slavery,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emancipated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, * K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAtiqN","text_ar":"عَاتِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotaqN","text_ar":"مُعْتَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;) and some of the relaters of traditions say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEotuwqN","text_ar":"مَعْتُوقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) but this is not allowable: (Msb, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqapN","text_ar":"عَتِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to a female, (S, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqN","text_ar":"عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also: Msb:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqN","text_ar":"عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EutaqaA='u","text_ar":"عُتَقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EitaAqN","text_ar":"عِتَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also sometimes occurs, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiraAmN","text_ar":"كِرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kariymN","text_ar":"كَرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqapN","text_ar":"عَتِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EataAy^iqu","text_ar":"عَتَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEatiyqu","text_ar":"العَتِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation applied to Es-Siddeek, (S, K,) i. e. (S) to Aboo-Bekr, (S, O, K,) as a surname, (K,) because he was said by the Prophet to be freed ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eatiyq","text_ar":"عَتِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":") from the fire [of Hell]: or because of his beauty, or comeliness: (S, O, K:) or he was so named by his mother. (O, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Old;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, L, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAtiqN","text_ar":"عَاتِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) the former is applied in this sense to anything, even to a man: (S, L:) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EitaAqN","text_ar":"عِتَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which occurs in a trad. applied to the earlier verses of the Kur-án that were revealed at Mekkeh, (L, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EutoqN","text_ar":"عُتْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, *) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EutuqN","text_ar":"عُتُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two dammehs, (Mgh, Msb,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burudN","text_ar":"بُرُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariydN","text_ar":"بَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) applied to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraAhim","text_ar":"دَرَاهِم"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EutoqN","text_ar":"عُتْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being [probably] a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EutuqN","text_ar":"عُتُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodN","text_ar":"بُرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burudN","text_ar":"بُرُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") and in like manner applied to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danaAniyr","text_ar":"دَنَانِير"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eut~aqN","text_ar":"عُتَّقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in the TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sm","text_ar":"سم"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with general analogy if pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAtiqN","text_ar":"عَاتِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eut~uqN","text_ar":"عُتُّقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two dammehs and teshdeed, is a mistake. (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albayotu AlEatiyqu","text_ar":"البَيْتُ العَتِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Kaabeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) given to it in the Kur-án [xxii. 30 and 34, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Old House"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (O,) because it was the first house founded upon the earth, (O, K,) as is said in the Kur [iii. 90]: (O:) or [as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Freed House,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because it was freed from submersion (O, K) in the days of the Deluge, (O,) being taken up; (TA;) or from the imperious, overbearing, or tyrannical, of mankind; or from the Abyssinians; or because not possessed by any one; (O, K;) and [thus expl.] it is tropical. (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanoTarapN EatiyqapN","text_ar":"قَنْطَرَةٌ عَتِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An old bridge"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, O, K,) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanoTarapN jadiydN","text_ar":"قَنْطَرَةٌ جَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the contr.], (S, O, K,) without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqapN","text_ar":"عَتِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the meaning of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilapN","text_ar":"فَاعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiydN","text_ar":"جَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the meaning of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlapN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAHN EatiyqN","text_ar":"رَاحٌ عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqapN","text_ar":"عَتِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAtiqN","text_ar":"عَاتِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Old wine"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamorN EaAtiqN","text_ar":"خَمْرٌ عَاتِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyqN","text_ar":"عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EutaAqN","text_ar":"عُتَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good and old wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, in a later portion of the art.:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAtiqN","text_ar":"عَاتِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old"},{"kind":"text","text":"wine: (S, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long kept in its receptacle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which no one has broken the seal"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the mouth of its jar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has just attained to maturity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA:) Hassán says, [using it as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates,]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kaA@lomisoka taxoliTuhu bimaA='i saHaAbapK\n                      \n                     \n                        A^awo EaAtiqK kadami Al*~abiyHi mudaAmi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like musk which thou mixest with the water of a cloud, or old"},{"kind":"text","text":"wine (&c.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the blood of the slaughtered"},{"kind":"text","text":"animal,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made to continue long"},{"kind":"text","text":"in its unopened jar]. (S, O, TA: but the last, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxoliTuhu","text_ar":"تَخْلِطُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxotaliTN","text_ar":"مُخْتَلِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEatiyqu","text_ar":"العَتِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine"},{"kind":"text","text":"[itself]. (K.) And ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ilaA='u","text_ar":"الطِّلَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expressed juice of grapes boiled until the quantity thereof is reduced to one third"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1948},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sort of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male palm-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the female palm-tree will not shake off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drop, its fruit"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tanofuDu naxolatuhu","text_ar":"لَا تَنْفُضُ نَخْلَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (K, TA.) ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN EatiyqN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jay~idu AlHbkpi","text_ar":"جَيِّدُ الحبكةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jay~idu AlHaboki","text_ar":"جَيِّدُ الحَبْكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, well woven"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","S","Mgh","O","AHn","K","L","Z"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}